#### Modern computers are electronic devices filled with lots of tiny wires. These wires carry electricity and at any moment a wire can be on or off. As a result, computers must represent information using either "on" or "off".  

#### Computers have their own binary system - they represent "on" or "off" using 0‚Äôs and 1‚Äôs. This is why you may have heard that computer science is all ‚Äú0‚Äôs and 1‚Äôs‚Äù. When you have a single 0 or 1, that is called one **bit** of information.

